Gm! At the start of the week we collected some questions from our community, now it's time to post the answers üëá

@Deril1160445 Asks - "Will the upcoming 2.0 sequencer support Cairo (Starknet)?"

Answer: We'll be looking at integrating any non-EVM chains which have demonstrated sufficient adoption and where we think native developers could benefit most from leveraging Reactive contracts. 

We aren't just limited to non-EVM chains however as we'll be adding the ability to subscribe to off-chain data too! We'll share more as we move closer to our first non-EVM integration.

@cryptodaaddy Asks - "how does Reactive handle cross-chain communication?"

Answer: Reactive enables cross-chain communication by combining our event-driven Reactive contract architecture with decentralized messaging infrastructure (GMPs) allowing smart contracts to react to events on one blockchain and trigger logic on another. Trustlessly, automatically and with no manual intervention!

@Romynft Asks - "What‚Äôs the biggest challenge you‚Äôre facing right now?"

Answer: While projects across the blockchain space face many challenges currently, Reactive specifically is well positioned to help address some of these problems, especially when faced with a high degree of fragmentation between chains and a greater need for coordination than ever before.

The challenges we're focusing on right now are to overcome the various technical hurdles needed to take Reactive to the next level, to introduce the foundations needed to begin non-EVM and off-chain data integrations and improvements to our own consensus mechanisms.

@outboxing13 Asks - "How has testing being going for the Ethereum EIL testnet?"

Answer: EIL itself is still in the very early stages so there's not too much to share just yet, however our focus is to ensure we stay up to date with any developments on Ethereum to ensure we can position ourselves best as an infrastructure provider in that ecosystem. 

@outboxing13 Asks - "Will you ever make staking similar to solana where we can leave it staked as long as we want?"

Answer: Users are likely to see big changes in many areas related to staking in the future as we restructure our current model, we can't commit to any specifics just yet though.

@Z37350A Asks - "What happened to shogun? Is this still an ongoing project?"

Answer: Certainly, we're still working with their team and will share updates on their RC integration as soon as it's available but we'll have to leave general updates on their project up to their team, we're sure they'd be happy to share more if you contact them directly however.

@ap_2331 Asks - "Any update on non-EVM integration?"

Answer: The first big component needed for non-EVM chains is sequencer 2.0 which is currently one of our development teams top priorities so you'll definitely be hearing more updates from us in the coming year as soon as it's ready to share.

We hope this answers all of your questions, as usual we'll return next Monday to collect more. Until then, have a great weekend!
